theorem
  for X being set, f, g being Function st f c= g & X c= dom f holds f|X
  = g|X
proof
  let X be set, f, g be Function;
  assume that
A1: f c= g and
A2: X c= dom f;
  thus f|X = g|(dom f)|X by A1,Th64
    .= g|(X/\ dom f) by RELAT_1:100
    .= g|X by A2,XBOOLE_1:28;
